data.description: Welcome to this East Hill gem, nestled amidst a row of multi-million dollar homes on prestigious Blackshear Ave. This extraordinary property offers an unrivaled combination of timeless charm, breathtaking views, and an unbeatable location. As you step inside, you'll be greeted by a sense of boundless energy and possibility. The spacious open concept design creates a seamless flow between the living, dining, and kitchen areas, perfect for both entertaining and everyday living. The tile work in the kitchen was done by a famous local ceramic artist, Peter King. The vaulted ceilings elevate the ambiance, exuding an air of grandeur and spaciousness. Natural light cascades through the generous windows, bathing the entire home in a warm, inviting glow while also allowing one to look down onto the Bayou. The three large bedrooms provide comfort and privacy as they're down the hall from the living area. The primary boasts a large walk-in closet and spacious bathroom. As for the bones, between the original brick and added stucco is an extra layer of insulation, keeping you cool in the summer heat & warm in the winter. Speaking of cool, this home is heated and cooled from a system of chillers instead of your traditional Hvac system. These help to save energy costs and the environment! This system works off of heat pump systems without the air-handlers and ductwork. The back patio is spacious and private as well, and the back yard does has room for a pool. Embrace a lifestyle of luxury and leisure, as you're just minutes away from both the pristine shores of Pensacola Beach and the vibrant heartbeat of downtown Pensacola. Schedule your showing today!
